  "text": "Research in project studies has become richer and more diverse, both theoretically and empirically. While we welcome such pluralism, we also contend that project studies, like many other subdisciplines of management and organization, is in risk of fragmentation and balkanization. In this regard, just as the theory of the firm would raise questions regarding why do firms exist, we, similarly, need to be able to answer the question why does the project studies exist? What integrates us? What are our boundaries? Following Knudsen (2003)'s call for balancing integration and pluralism in social science, and its developed in the field of project studies by [CITATION_1] , pluralism should be accompanied by integration efforts across the field. We therefore call for 'pluralism with a focus'.",
